In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims October 2016 as National Arts and Humanities Month. He highlights the importance of the arts and humanities in driving progress and shaping the American narrative. The arts and humanities provoke thought, encourage creativity and innovation, and connect people around the world. Obama emphasizes the need to prioritize and invest in the arts and humanities, especially for young people. He calls upon the people of the United States to observe the month with appropriate ceremonies, activities, and programs to celebrate the arts and humanities.